place_description: High Octane Coffee Creamery Eatery is the newest Union County’s Newest and Hottest Foodie Location. Offers 100% Specialty Colombian Coffee, Hersheys Ice Cream, Sandwiches, pastries, smoothies,parfaits and acai bowls.

reviews_data.review_text: Such a cute coffee shop! Wife and I decided to stop in after a playdate introduced us to High Octane coffee. The place is really cute and atmospheric.  Old gas station turned coffee shop. Coffee was great. Blueberry scone was buttery, blueberry-y, and the croissant sandwich was delicious. We had a great time and look to be back since we can get a nice little morning date in before work.
The baristas were extremely friendly and quick with my wife's and I coffee. The coffee was amazing!!
Made a quick stop for coffee. Great menu and vibe. Coffee was good and service was on point. Would definately recommend.

Our first time here.  This place is ADORABLE!!!  A gas station turned into a coffee and ice cream place.  They have a good variety of coffee, smoothies, sandwiches and waffles.    We ordered drinks.   I got the peppermint mocha iced coffee which was DELICIOUS!  My daughter got the white chocolate matcha, which was THUMBS UP AMAZING!  The staff was very friendly and helpful!!  Looking forward to coming back!

Update.   We stopped back to try the ice cream.  My daughter had the vanilla and I had the Salty Caramel Truffle.  My ice was FABULOUS and DELICIOUS!!!!!!!
Welcoming and clean with vintage charm and their espresso is excellent quality!
Best in Monroe
It's cute and the staff are friendly. They have a wide variety of food and beverages. I loved their black forest latte and acai bowls.
Great vibes fresh well made food and good coffee I had an everything bagel with bec and they were able to make me a shaken espresso just by telling them what's in the drink love this place 10/10
Very cute place inside to sit and hang out. The food and coffee is delicious and the service is great! Everyone that works there is very nice.

We were in Monroe and came across this place.  Loved the nostalgia and it really drew us in.  We ordered from the menu a Thanksgiving sandwich, a ham biscuit  and a BLT.  Both sandwiches came with a bag of chips. We didn't order drinks. We ordered one medium ice cream cone.  Maybe we made the wrong food choices, but we wouldn't order these again.  The service was very good and friendly.  I will say $50.00 for this order seemed extremely high for what we received.  The ice cream cone was 2 scoops and large, but right at $8.00 seemed a bit much.  I think we should of just ordered coffee.  It seems that is what most people get here.  We had already gotten coffee at a place on Main Street which was really good, so we skipped the drinks here.  We wanted to love this place and it wasn't crowded at lunchtime.  Unfortunately,  we probably wouldn't go here again, except to try their coffee.
Beautiful waffles and great coffee. Yummy salads.

My wife and I like boutique coffee joints, but we have had issues finding one in Union County we like until now!

Coffee: This is about the coffee for us and it's really good! It's smooth and tasty. I don't usually like my coffee bitter, so the white mocha is perfect for me. They can make it extra sweet but it was a bit too sweet.

Chai: Any time my wife talks about chai, she is comparing it to her favorite chai from college. She compared it to that chai! I even liked it and I don't like chai!

Food: My wife I have tried the breakfast sandwiches only, and they were pretty good. I had a bacon, egg, and cheese on sourdough. She had a turkey, egg, and cheese on GLUTEN FREE BREAD! I don't know if they use separate grills, so there might be cross contamination, but my wife had no issues with it.

Atmosphere: The location in a restored gas station is genius! The soft chairs right in the entrance are perfect and there is outside seating when the weather is good. This place is popular, so do be prepared for a possible long wait if you go in during peak hours

Staff: They are fairly friendly. They normally have a smile, repeat your order back to you, get your order to you quickly, and check on you if things are taking too long.

They consistently stay open and make quality drinks and food. This is the best coffee in Union County and the best chai in the South!

Recently found this little place. BEST iced chai latte in NC I have had. I get it with almond milk and cinnamon on top. I've lived in Monroe for a few years and been looking for a chai like this. Also, I have tried their fruit bowls and the breakfast sandwich with gluten free bread. Everything has tasted great! Also pictured is a breakfast sandwich with regular bread. So excited to have found this place!
Once again the Turkey Ruben was the best sandwich i've had in many years

Been visiting Monroe and decided to stop and have lunch at this place. I admit that good reviews and ratings attracted me to do so. I ordered Choco Cookie frappe and it was good, Thanksgiving sandwich was ok but bread was burnt for my liking, but edible. Now the stuff wasn't very welcoming, so as prices on food and drinks. We ended up paying 50$ for two sandwiches with processed deli meat and drinks, absolutely ridiculous. They don't offer variety of milk so be aware of it if. Parking limited, you have to park behind restaurant on town parking.

Extra info to my review: Had lunch in Dilworth area in Charlotte, order of chicken sandwich with real meat and lamb burger with two coffees cost us 40$ tip included. Place called Kid Cashew.
Nothing really special about this place. Don't understand the high ratings. Coffee was decent, food was average. $13 for a sandwich and a salad in Monroe was outrageous.
This was one of the best cafes I've been to the staff was super nice and the food and coffee was wonderful!
Drive through only.
Egg and cheese croissant tasted good
Just moved to the area and I'm extremely glad that this coffee shop is around.

Cute place! Clean, vintage vibes, although not sure if they have AC or if it was out cause it was a bit warm inside.

I tried the Thanksgiving sandwich and a London Fog latte. Both were well prepared but the flavors were pretty bland, especially  given the prices were on the higher end.

Service was a little slow and not particularly upbeat.

Can't speak to the pastries or ice cream. But they looked good!

Plenty of parking. There isn't a lot of space between tables if you are visiting with wheelchairs or need a little extra body space.
I love to go up here I enjoy the atmosphere the stuff are fantastic and they take pride in their work which actually means a lot to me.

Oscar and his team are always courteous and professional.  We've visited half a dozen times but enjoy the early mornings mostly because it's not too crowded.  I really like black coffee and their Columbian 'Washed' bean is some of the best black coffee strength I've ever had.  Oscar said they have different flavors each day; we bought Washed and Bourbon whole beans today, and he gave us a sample bag of the Gesha to try also.  Can't wait.

BTW, my favorite sandwich is the turkey Rueben.  Enjoy good food, good atmosphere, and great customer service.
We've been here a couple of times, and each time, the coffee and food are wonderful. Great little stop!
Great variety of delicious breakfast, sandwiches and coffee brews.

Unique coffee shop plus in an old gas station. Coffee and food were good. Does get a bit cramped when large groups or customers are waiting for their orders. Could use another line or spot for pickup.
This is a destination spot, meaning "get in the car and go". Very cool the way they have themed it. And Oscar knows his coffee! Food great, as well.
I love it here. The coffee and food are always delicious. The staff is so kind and attentive.

Amazing place to get coffee and food the Barsitas are amazing!!! I just went there a couple of days ago and and I met one of the owners he was a Barista a true Barista he knew about so much about the coffee history he was truly a good hard worker and loved what he does the Barista at the cash register too she was really sweet I tipped and will do it again!!
Love the food and the service !!!!

The cutest little coffee shop.  First time visiting here, so we were not sure what to expect.  The outside is adorable.  We had to sit outside on their little patio because we had our dog with us.  Inside was very crowded which was a great thing for them.

The coffee was so good and we split the Carmel Waffle which was amazing!!!  It's big so you can definately share.  2 coffee drinks and one dessert with tip was $30.  It's a little pricey, so for us it would not be for all the time because let's face it, you cannot come here just for coffee, because everything looks absolutely delicious .

When we are by this area again, we will definately stop back!!

The place is very well decorated but this place is a great example of the low barrier to entry for coffee places. People open coffee places because it's cheaper than starting other businesses and many times they don't know what they are doing. Let's take as an example their "honey lavender" flavored drink. If you put a whole ounce of the lavender  it tastes like floor cleaner. One is only supposed to put a touch in. Well this place doesn't care and they just dump an ounce in. When I went to order something different, even though the mistake was theirs, they let me order another nine dollar drink. Also when I was sitting down and the new drink was delivered, I asked that they take the old drink away. The server looked at me like I was an idiot, and spoke to like I was an idiot saying "the trash is right there, you can do it yourself". I asked the server if I was supposed to dump this whole drink in the trash and then it would leak all over the floor when they emptied it, and there was a sink in back. The server took it with a huff.

This is my second visit to this place and each time I left having spent way too much money for a below average product and service. It does look cool though, and things that look cool sometimes aren't cool.

Came to NC from Australia to take my child to University and found this awesome cafe in Monroe. I highly recommend their coffee and bagels, with bacon, egg & cheese. The rest of the menu options looked awesome too. I was in search of good coffee after having Starbucks and scooters. Their staff were very friendly aswell, the vibe is cool and setting is comfortable. My daughter will definitely be bringing her college friends down to try. I wish your business much success - High Octane cafe. God bless.

Atomsphere here is awesome. I encourage small unique business and that is what this place is. Restored 1940's gas station full of antiques of the years passed with a clean modern look and modern amenities is a winner in my book. Then comes the food!  !! Oh yah unique cookfood that isn't your typical frozen to fryer it's real fresh food cooked to order. Even the food presentation is awesome. Over all an example of what eating experience should be. Prices are fair too! Rather give my money to a local business like this than some franchise. This place has charm and character. Highly recommend it.
Excellent coffee! Excellent and friendly service,! I had a breakfast sandwich on a croissant, it was so good! love the place!!!

We were going to meet for coffee at another place but they didn't offer food . We were both famished so decided to take a chance and walked down the street to High Octane. We were so happy!! I was able to get a gluten-free breakfast sandwich that was grilled and very delicious.  A. got a beautiful looking croissant/ brioche sandwich, she said it was yummy. She also got a coffee, she's a connoisseur, and immediately raved to the barista that it was delicious. I got a sugar-free hazelnut latte, so so good. 
I hope more people will discover this cute little spot. The staff were really friendly and efficient. From the outside, it's really difficult to tell that it's an eatery. It used to be a gas station and it's adorable, how they decorated.

This place is truly remarkable. Service, Atmosphere, & Food is wonderful!. For the family, or just YOU this place is great. Their sandwiches to their Affogato to their Nutella, Banana, Strawberry waffles, and dozens of other amazingness things they have! This is the spot for breakfast or lunch or just a treat!
My family loves all their treats and first class service.
Love the name love the coffee
Delicious sandwiches and smoothies! Loved everything we tried!
The coffee is okay. Frappuccino was too sweet. Great environment. I'd love to see this business be successful. I'm so glad they remodeled this old station!
A bit pricey for the area. Absolutely amazing coffee and food. Great service with a smile. Good for families or a quick stop for caffeine.
Love the waffles there. Sandwiches are ok but waffles 10/10. Add ice cream to it! Their frappes and ice coffees are also great. I love the theme and the patio. Park behind the building.

This coffee shop is fabulous!  Wifi, top-notch gas station kitsch decor, boho ceramics, flawless caramel macchiato-+this place is pure "Aaaahhhh" from the moment you drive up.  Plenty of kid-friendly AND healthy options, with reusable cups and trays, this place hits the marks!
I absolutely love this place. A true gem in Historic Monroe. If you haven't already, TRY IT!!! The little Havana sandwich is the best version in all of Charlotte and surrounding areas!
A very cute place! I got a ham and cheese croissant and the coffee was amazing. I even bought a bag to bring home till make for myself. I definitely recommend!
Fun, fast, great breakfast and coffee. Brings on the nostalgia!
Love the choco vanilla milkshake. Would recommend!
Fun place, pricy coffee but tasty food and a cute shop overall.  A good ice cream selection too!
The staff was really friendly and welcoming. Lots of variety for treats. Quaint little place.

The pastries/sweets here are UNMATCHED! My favorite is the Tres Leches cake, but I have yet to have anything that isn't absolutely delicious. My favorite coffee is the honey and lavender latte. Great study and hang out spot!

Not local to Monroe but wanted to try a local coffee shop in search for a great Chai Tea Latte!  High Octane was sure to please!  One of the best Ive ever had!  Super cute place, friendly staff!  Make sure to check them out when in Monroe!
If you're ever in Monroe North Carolina best ice coffee around

I have been here a few times but each time no improvement with wait times. The coffee and food are okay but not good enough to wait 10 minutes for a coffee. Also it is a bit pricey compared to other coffee shops in the area. Not likely to be back anytime soon.
Super cute place. Awesome latte!  Best I've had in a long time. Great pastry. Can't wait to go back and try a waffle or the lunch menu.
Wonderful coffee, delicious sweets and sandwiches! Friendly staff that keep the place very clean. Great specialty items and a beautiful space filled with light and unique decor.
This place doesn't dissapointed. It's a lovely quaint cafe atmosphere with great food and a huge menu option. The people have always been super nice and it's just a joy to be in.
Such a fun atmosphere & delicious coffee!
Nutella waffle was amazing!!
Fantastic vibe and atmosphere, definitely going to return

There are so many things to offer here, it's incredible! Breakfast, a variety of waffles, sandwiches, coffee, desserts, and ice cream too! Please don't hesitate to check this place out. It is so neat inside and out, and an outstanding atmosphere. They even have Cornhole by their outdoor seating! Plenty of parking out back, and open all day/evening as well. Definitely a great addition to downtown Monroe.

This is the cutest coffee shop ever! It's nestled in a renovated gas station.. eclectic environment
Coffee was delicious, matcha frappe ( I had them mix with caramel macchiato)
I took my cousin & we shared a huge waffle.. we even got to talk to the owner of the building as he was sitting with wife, & family!
Visit here! You won't regret it!
Everything was delicious service was great will make my new regular coffee spot!
Great coffee awesome waffles !! Great service!
Amazing waffles!! We tried the Nutella waffle with bananas and strawberries and the creamy strawberries waffle and both were delicious!! Super cute coffee shop!

Unbelievable coffee. Stopped in for coffee for myself and ice cream for my kids. Their ice cream was wonderful and my iced vanilla latte was the absolute best I've ever had. The ladies working were super nice and I can't wait to come back!
I recommend the affogato! Very good, espresso was great. The milkshakes look great too.

Came for lunch and it was awesome!! Staff were kind, patient (so many yummy options I was contemplating what to get!!)  and even brought coffee and food to me. Also very clean!! The Milky Way latte was PERFECT! I had a breakfast sandwich and it was AMAZING. I don't leave reviews but this place deserves one!! I can't wait to go back

I love this restaurant it is amazing the food was delicious and the employees are very friendly. I would definitely recommend this place if you love waffles and sandwiches. They also have an ice cream bar with everyone's favorite flavors.

We love this place! They do everything on point! The service is good and everyone who works here is so friendly. We have tried most of their sandwiches and love them all. You can also get amazing coffee here as well as pasties, ice cream and waffles! The atmosphere is cozy and inviting. We will definitely be back soon!

The waffles are always on point.
1 Chaco cookie Frappuccino
1 brown sugar cinnamon coffee cloud
Theee best coffee in Town! Their sandwiches and pastries are pretty amazing. Can only recommend them!
Cute coffee shop with great options for food and dessert!!
Wonderful establishment, love having them in the downtown area. Great people and spot!

This  place is so adorable . Very clean, service is great. The sandwiches were hand made, very fresh and tasty. It was our first time on Valentine's Day but it will be a favorite spot for a great sandwich in the future.
Lo mejor!

Had a lovely time at High Octane Coffee. The staff was exceptionally kind; they not only brought my coffee to me as a courtesy (something rarely seen at cafes nowadays), but they also noticed how bright it was where I was sitting- they went as far as to untie the curtains so I could look at my computer properly, and not before asking if I was alright with that.  It's very clear that the employees here are kind and attentive. The coffee I also bought, a caramel macchiato, was great! I am excited to go back soon and try their waffles. Last, but certainly not least, the atmosphere here is beautiful and really clean.

This little old gas station converted into this coffee shop and deli only adds to the small town charm of Monroe but brings in that contemporary feel of a newer age. The food is simple but delicious, and the coffee is wonderful, and to only add to this charming place, they offer ice cream and breakfast all day. The service is wonderful, and the atmosphere allows you to have a small town vibe with a new young culture. The only downside is the limited parking; but there is parking on the streets and sidewalks to walk from downtown, just a few blocks away.
I love this place!  Great food,  great service,  beautifully restored Sinclair Station!
Great place for everyone!

Love this retrofitted gas station. Super sweet owners. Food, coffee and ice cream is amazing. Loving the atmosphere in Monroe with little places like this. Fair prices as well. Definitely check it out!

So excited to find this unique and loving restored gas station, now serving delicious coffees, ice cream, sandwiches and treats. We were looking for some refreshments after a great show at the Dowd Theatre and found this gem (within walking distance). Onsite parking is available, but is limited. Service was quick and friendly. There were so many great options on the menu that we will have to return and bring the rest of the family!  Highly recommended.
My visit was very good.
This cute little shop has the most amazing sandwich i've ever had, that's big coming from someone who avoids sandwiches in general. It's a must try, the New York mood is absolutely incredible

Cappuccino was great, although like most places it was prepared like a latte, but that's no big deal. Smooth espresso flavor. The red velvet muffin was delicious. Next time I'm in town, I'll definitely be back to try another baked item or lunch.
The creamy strawberries waffles with banana as an add on was amazing. Also the BLT with turkey added is also a new favorite. Highly recommend. A nice plus is they serve you.
It looks like an old Sinclair gas station but has the best coffee and waffles and the sandwiches look amazing also. The waffles are the best I ever had,  covered in strawberries and ice cream
I love this place!!!
Great coffee and food. 3 meat sandwich  was really good.
Really good croissant and gingerbread latte! Service staff was very nice, just got a little crowded but overall really cute coffee shop with ample seating.

Great coffee!! Owned and operated by a Colombian family that owns a coffee farm in Colombia!! The freshest single origin coffee you could ask for! They are less expensive than the coffee shops in the area. By far the best coffee in Monroe. You will get more than your money's worth at High Octane.

12/1/23 - This is the place for people who love coffee. I doesn't matter how their coffee is prepared (espresso, drip, cold brew...) it is all so good. Now they have breakfast sandwiches!!
Haven't had coffee this good since I moved up here from Florida, and it's in the cutest old gas station with the Sinclair dinosaur!! But the coffee was phenomenal and so is there ice cream

I had a Nutella Waffle with a Cappuccino and it was amazing! The atmosphere, quality, service and the waiting time was excellent! They have high chairs for the little ones, patio for the furry ones, and also se habla espanol.

Fully recommend.

The building and decor were great, coffee was really good but that's were it ends. I ordered a sausage egg and cheese sandwich it was a processed egg patty, frozen sausage patty on a bun it took about 20 mins and they first gave my sandwich to another customer. Not sure were they get the pastries from but they were nothing to speak of either. Oh well we tried it and sadly won't be going back.

Good coffee, the bean tastes very nice, and the drinks are yummy. The pastries and sandwiches are really delightful too. The place is cute on the inside, too. But the real star? The guy making drinks. This barista was whipping people's drinks out like mad at the Christmas parade rush, and they did not lack an ounce in quality. It was like he was creating art. Honestly 10/10 for the dedication and speed at the hands of such chaos, for all the workers. I plan to go back!
Really enjoyed this place! Love the variety and friendly service.
Fun place! Good service and good food.
Great food, coffee and always liked the old nostalgic gasoline pumps.
This was my first time going with my friend! I enjoyed it. The atmosphere was so nice and everyone was friendly! The decor is so cute and absolutely loved the food & coffee!
Hands down best caramel macchiato I've ever had. Cute little spot and spacious, love it here !

I took my wife here for breakfast. We order two drinks, 2 sandwiches, and a muffin, and that cost $50??
Then I sat and waited for 30 minutes for the food, after they forgot one of the sandwiches.
As I was sitting and waiting, I noticed the 92 health sanitation score. Yikes.

After the loooong wait, the overpriced food, and the health score. I will not be coming back here.
There wasn't even anyone in line in front of us. Why in the world did I sit for 30 minutes waiting on a to go order.
Grabbed lunch here. Great coffee and sandwiches. Topped it off with some yummy ice cream, too! If we lived in Monroe, we'd be regulars :)
Had a great ice cream cone! The parking is a little strange and there seems to be very little accessible entry?
Think Retro but Today's World of Coffee, Dinks, Food and Ice Cream!
So amazing! They support the right people. Amazing place. Great ice cream and coffee!!!!!

Nice coffee-ice cream shop inside a repurposed old gas station in Monroe, North Carolina...Very good sandwiches...Nice assortment of baked good...They take cash and cards...Extremely friendly customer service!
This place was amazing! The sandwiches were delicious, the iced pumpkin latte was great. The service was great!
This place is so cute! And everyone was kind. If you're the moms who weren't watching your kids as they tried to trash the corn hole boards, shame on you!
Super clean spot, cozy, awesome atmosphere, great friendly staff, yummy food!!!
This place is a gem! The owner was so sweet came a greeted us personally. The staff was super sweet, attentive and friendly and the food was super delicious . Will definitely come back!
it was our first time going today, the food was amazing & fresh, the people were so friendly, and the coffee was rich and delicious. 10/10 would recommended and definitely coming back!

A small town gas station converted into an uptown ice cream and coffee bar. You will want to sit down and take it all in (especially after a waffle covered in fruit and ice cream). If you love memoribilia or food, its worth the visit!

Best latte ever!!! Their coffee is amazing! Really genuine service and great vibe and atmosphere. Love that they converted a gas station into a fresh space with delicious coffee, sandwiches and ice cream. Will definitely be back!

I joined my family here for ice cream, but they have so many more options. Coffee, pastries, sandwiches. Waffles, not waffle cones, actual waffles, and ice cream.
Definitely want to try the Little Havana because who doesn't love a good cubano?
This is a family owned and operated business so I am looking forward to visiting again.
Great place for a sandwich and coffee! Great service!
Love Oscar and his crew. Great place!  High quality and great atmosphere.
Great coffee and gotta love a place that serves breakfast sandwiches all day!
Amazing Coffee!
Adorable coffee shop with a great staff and wonderful atmosphere. Ice americano was delicious.
Very friendly service with good pastries and coffee
Es un lugar muy agradable y acogedor para estar en familia, muy buena la comida. Y muy atentos.

Awesome coffee house in a restored gas station. The owners are so nice! They get fresh coffee beans from Columbia! I recommend the affogato. And also got the cappuccino crunch ice cream with milk and a shot of espresso (pictured). Give it a try!

Highly Recommend this tasty spot! They have a great selection of coffee, pastries, ice cream and sandwiches.

We came here for sandwiches and coffees on a cute couples date.

Tried The Little Havana sandwich. This one turned out to be my favorite.

We also tried the Queso Planche which comes in second place.

Third favorite we tried was the Thanksgiving sandwich. Very nice combo of flavors.

Last thing was the new breakfast sandwich which has bacon, egg, and cheese but that wasn't as exciting as their other creations.

We got sugar free vanilla and hazelnut syrups in our iced lattes with almond milk. Those were very nice. Great amount of coffee, milk, and sweetness. Nice blend of flavors.

We also got a handful of pastries to test out and see what was good. I recommend trying any of them and enjoying them all or come by a few times to try something new every time.

Loved the inside vibe and some cool things in here to see.

Service was exceptional as well!
My boyfriend and I absolutely love coming here!! He started taking me here last month and I am completely obsessed! From customer service to the quality of food, you'll never EVER be disappointed!!
Friendly staff, great food, and even better coffee. Waffles, sandwiches, and espresso on point!! Love the 50s garage styling, partly as I am a car guy, but you'll love it too.

Been there twice since they opened. First time although it took WAY to long, the sandwiches were really good! Second time, the line was too long and not moving, so we left without eating. They really need to get faster or hire more staff....or both!

Very rarely do I give 5 Star to any business. But this is off the charts good!
The food - fresh ingredients, very well prepared, and delicious!

The drink - does Columbian coffee mean anything to you? If not, best coffee in the world!

The service - take a trip back to the 80s, and feel at home with this family owned business. Friendly, knowledgeable, and they WANT your business.

The atmosphere - see it to believe it. An old style gas station converted into a modern but cozy eatery! This is what is all about!

And top it all off - The story
Family owned business where the owners sold everything to invest in this amazing place. This is not just another business. This is a one of a kind fairy tale story that you have to come and experience for yourself!

Such a beautiful place. I love the decor in there. The drinks are amazing and the carrot cake is super moist and the icing isn't too sweet just the way I like it. The workers are very nice and make sure your token care of aswell.

Cute place, great coffee, and tasty treats!
Love having another place to add to my coffee place rotation!

The service was amazing, everyone was super nice and professional!

I had the iced latte which was delicious and I tried the blackberry mojito scone and churro, both were tasty.

My sister in law had one of their sandwiches and enjoyed it!

Great coffee, atmosphere, and staff! Everyone was so friendly! Josh went above and beyond to explain the different beans offered, how they're grown, and the best ways to brew them. The caramel macchiato was absolutely delicious, and everyone in my party really enjoyed their drinks. Looking forward to visiting again!

I met a friend for brunch here today, and absolutely loved the food, decor and how the owners preserved the integrity of the old gas station yet gave it a modern "facelift". I highly recommend everyone try this new coffee shop. There is something for everyone including delicious made-to-order sandwiches, pastries and desserts, a great variety of coffee options, plus ice cream!

My precious Moma took me to this new place she'd found and I'm so happy she did! As soon as we entered, we were welcomed with friendly, cheerful greetings and smiling faces. The decor and ambiance were great...making it a place you'd feel comfortable hanging around in for a bit. They're kind of a one stop shop, having ice cream, sandwiches, pastries, specialty coffees, waffles, etc..I ordered a plain waffle with just butter and syrup (I wasn't feeling too adventurous that day) and The Moma ordered a Strawberry-Banana-Ice cream-Waffle confectionary delight. My waffle was delightfully golden and crispy on the outside and so fluffy on the inside!! Moma was making sounds I wasn't old enough to hear and then...I took a sip of my coffee and it was pure Heaven!!! I will be back again and again and...
Coffee shop is fancy without the expensive prices please come get some coffee from here
Super cute coffee shop and eatery. I had the French press coffee, and it was delicious!
We dropped by just for coffee and had a good time.  I read you will now  feature dairy-free ice cream and we hope you will continue to offer sugar-free ice cream as well.

Nice place to hang out with family.   We tried different ice cream and enjoyed every one of them.  They also sale coffee and food.  I definitely want to go back and try the coffee and food.  The staff was welcoming and friendly!
excellent service overall!!!! & great staff!!

Great new place to eat in Monroe. Met the owner today who came out and asked how everything was and a bit about his story. Really appreciated him taking time to ask. Staff was friendly, the waffle was excellent, the roast beef on marble rye was also excellent. Oh yea, a nice selection of tasty pastries. Will be going back.

Stopped in to check them out. Great owners! Staff were friendly and helpful! Place looked beautiful and the sandwich I had was delicious and for sure gave me my money's worth. I don't know where this one star review has been, but when a new place opens you have to be patient and understanding to the folks working. To wait five minutes isn't the end of the world and it's made to order.....please be patient and polite to the folks who have opened a new establishment to service you and others. I will for sure be back and look forward to trying other items and coffee! Thanks for the experience, great food and opening in our town!
Welcome to Monroe!

This place is a one of a kind! They have coffee, ice cream, and sandwiches. I haven't tried the sandwiches but the ice cream and coffee is satisfactory. The theme of this place really adds to the whole experience.

Fantastic selection friendly knowledgeable service. I can't wait to travel through town again and share my experiences with others at this wonderful coffee shop. I love that they have converted this old gas station into something extremely useful and very yummy
#cindersadventures #artioadventures

We had lunch, coffee and ice cream today, and we had the best experience!  Everyone was helpful, kind, and welcoming. Everything we ate/drank was fantastic, and the prices were spot on. We'll definitely be back very soon, and we wish them all the success in the world. This is exactly the type of business Monroe needs more of!
Genuinely the best espresso I have tried in Charlotte so far (including many specialty coffee shops). Laid back atmosphere, great food and South American desserts.
Excellent small place in downtown Monroe. Most go for coffee, I'm not a coffee drinker, but their sandwiches were excellent. Very friendly staff, they were quite busy but service was awesome.

My daughter in law and I came in today to get a drink they posted a picture of. It wasn't officially on the menu yet but they made us each one. We were the first to try the Strawberry Jam Frappe! Absolutely delicious.
Cute little spot. Food is good but could use some side options to go with the sandwiches other than the sad pile of lettuce. Try the Thanksgiving sandwich!
Such a cool little spot!

This is a new business, they opened up about a month ago.  The owners are very excited about being in the Monroe community.  I don't ever question someone else's raring, but I challenge the person that give a one star, to please give them another try.  I showed up unannounced with 30 high school students wanting ice cream and they served them and their regular customers.  Was there a small wait sure.   They are also growing their staff and seeking feedback from their customers.   Like one lady when I was there asked about lactose free ice cream.    I tried one of the sandwiches and it was very tasty.  This is a good place to stop and get a morning coffee, sandwich at lunch away from the crowds or an ice cream on a hot afternoon.
The waffle was super good! super friendly staff :) Alia was super nice

Had a Havana sandwich & a waffle! Omg they were both amazing. Take it from someone that's been to Belgium & had their waffles & lived in Miami with Cuban sandwiches. The taste was superb. I cannot wait to go back to try their coffees and ice cream. The service was great, they stop by our table to make sure we received everything. The ambiance was all that I could ask for in a shop like that, the decor and design is aesthetically pleasing! Will be back & I'll be bringing friends :) Anyone who rated 1 star for slow service needs to have some patience & take a chill pill.
Customer service was amazing and the food was even better !
The Hershey's ice cream was great, will be back

Great Chemex! made with Specialty Coffee from Colombia.
Friendly service.

This place is such a great concept! Coffee, small food menu and ice cream.
I had the Thanksgiving sandwich and it was delightful - perfect balance of sweet and savory! The side salad it was served with had a very tasty dressing as well. Can't wait to come back and try more of their offerings!
The staff was friendly and the atmosphere very unique. I love how they incorporated relics from the era that this old gas station was in operation.

I'm thrilled with this new addition to downtown Monroe! This coffee shop is hands down the best in town thanks to Oscar's expertise in the coffee industry, superb brewing techniques, and the exceptional quality of the coffee beans used at this location. I rarely take my coffee black, but I can here!

I haven't yet had the pleasure of trying any of the food options, but I've heard nothing but good things from those that have.

While my Chemex coffee took slightly longer to prepare during my first few visits, I fully appreciate that the business is still getting started and working out the kinks. Regardless, things have since gotten better, and the coffee continues to be absolutely worth the wait!

I've been twice now and neither time disappointed. The iced caramel macchiato is so good. The coffee is really smooth and perfectly sweetened. The Little Havana sandwich is yummy too! Perfectly grilled and delicious. Highly recommend trying this place out!
We had an awesome first visit! The coffee was great and the nutella waffle was really good!

The service was extremely slow and the workers were not friendly. We waited at the register for 5 minutes to get our order taken then another 10 minutes to get our coffee. The coffee was decent but definitely not worth the wait and hassle.
Slowest service ever!!!! 8 people working and it took them 20 minutes to get me a hot coffee. Never again. But they are in Monroe so I didn't expect much
The new hot spot for coffee and more in Monroe , bravo to all involved much needed place in historic downtown Monroe.
Loved it !
First time visit today and it was great! Sandwiches,  pan dulce, scones, ice cream, lots of coffee... this place is a great addition to downtown Monroe!

The coffee was buenisimo!!!  Oscar the owner was friendly and inviting, the team was friendly and helpful! We tried the Thanksgiving sandwich and hot lattes. Everything was   ! Soooo good will definitely be back!
The best way to starting the day. Or just a having something delicious for the evening.

I absolutely LOVE this place everything about it was fantastic!!  The service was some of the best I have ever received!! Every single person was so friendly and asked us how we enjoyed our experience and the coffee.
The coffee was absolutely AMAZING so delicious and fresh. The atmosphere was wonderful you feel like you step back in time almost.
This will definitely be a new favorite spot for me and my family I can't wait to go back!
